@deleted-role Alright, all changes have now been merged and SN30 has been entirely revamped! below is a list of every change that has been made
- Validators are now separated into two parts, the stress testing/weight setting and the request forwarder, the latter of which is vertically and horizontally scalable(via load balancing) allowing the subnet to not get bottlenecked under load from user requests
- Validators no longer download the generation results as part of their stress test, meaning they will no longer affect miner's scores with their networks
  - The packet sizes, for both the initial requests and the generation result downloads have been made greatly smaller, and are no longer encoded in any way before being sent over network
  - Miners hash their results and validators check said hash to ensure the generation was done at the correct point in the pipeline
- Miners now no longer have a separate image generation API, meaning you load balance directly to the miner(removing yet another bottleneck of one neuron to many GPUs)
- Miners store their generation results in redis until accessed for the first time, where they will be either downloaded & deleted or discarded based on cancellation
- The validators store their miner stress test results in redis
- Pathing logic works better now, you can start `main.py` files directly with python without using `-m module.main` like before
- The project entirely uses `poetry` now, as it appears to work better as a package manager than just purely `pip` and `setuptools`(more setup documentation & help scripts coming soon)
- A generic `update.sh` script has been made to be used as a `cron` job for auto-updating, compatible with both miners and validators(more documentation for that coming soon)
- VTrust issues should be reduced now as weights become more consistent with the validator's network affecting the stress test less
- Dual miner validators setups are now more possible, but no code is written specifically to support them yet
